Executive Profile
Mark T. Gallogly  Co-Founder and Managing Principal, Centerbridge Partners, L.P.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 3 different industries.See Board Relationships60--
Background

		Mr. Mark T. Gallogly is a Managing Principal of Centerbridge Partners L.P. Mr. Gallogly founded Centerbridge Partners in 2005. Mr. Gallogly served as an Investor Director at Freedom Communications, Inc. Previously, he served as Senior Managing Director and Head of Private Equity Group at Blackstone CCC Capital Partners LP and its affiliates. Prior to that, he served as a Senior Managing Director and Head of the Private Equity group at The Blackstone Group, Private Equity ... Group from 1994 to 2005. He served as the President and Chief Executive Officer at Blackstone Communication Advisors. Mr. Gallogly joined Blackstone Communication in 1989 and was responsible for and involved in the execution of nearly all of Blackstone’s communications and media investments. Prior to Blackstone, he served at Manufacturers Hanover Trust Company for nearly ten years and was a member of the Acquisition Finance Group. He serves on the Economic Recovery Advisory Board. He is a Member of Board of Overseers of Columbia Business School. He also served on Obama's Economic Recovery Board. He serves as a Director of The Partnership for New York City, Inc. He served as a Director of Dana Holding Corporation since January 2008 until August 2013. He served as a Director of Centennial Communications Corp. since January 7, 1999 and Commnet Cellular Inc. since February 1998. He served as a Director of Centennial Cellular Operating Co. LLC and FiberNet, LLC. He served as a Director of Wi-LAN Technologies Inc. He was employed at Saranac Capital Management LP. He is a Member of the limited liability company which acts as the General Partner of BCP CommNet LP. He received M.B.A. from Columbia University, received his B.A., with honors, from the University of Notre Dame in 1979 and attended Sophia University in Tokyo.Read Full Background




