Advisory Council
Mark T. Gallogly
Co-founder and Managing Principal, Centerbridge Partners












































































Mark T. Gallogly is Cofounder and Managing Principal of Centerbridge Partners. Centerbridge is an investment firm with $25 billion of assets under management. The firm is focused on private equity and credit investing. Prior to founding Centerbridge in partnership with Jeffrey H. Aronson in October 2005, Mr. Gallogly was with the Blackstone Group for 16 years. At Blackstone, he was most recently a Senior Managing Director, the head of private equity and a member of the firm’s management and investment committees.
Throughout his 30 year career in investing and finance, Mr. Gallogly has been involved in a broad spectrum of industries, businesses and investment cycles. Mr. Gallogly served on President Obama’s Council on Jobs and Competiveness from 2010 to 2012 and the President’s Economic Recovery Advisory Board from 2008 to 2010. He also currently serves on the advisory council of the Hamilton Project, an economic policy group at the Brookings Institution, the Columbia Business School Board of Overseers, and the board of trustees of the ROADS Charter Schools. He is a partner of the Partnership for New York City and member of the Council on Foreign Relations and the Economic Club of New York.
Mr. Gallogly graduated with honors from the University of Notre Dame and attended Sophia University in Tokyo. He received his MBA from Columbia Business School in 1986. Mr. Gallogly lives in New York City with his wife and three daughters.




